// Implement a GradeBook system:
//
// Class: Student
//   - String name, String id
//   - Constructor, getters, toString() -> "[id] name"
//
// Class: GradeBook<T extends Student>
//   - HashMap<T, ArrayList<Integer>> storing scores per student
//   - void enroll(T student): add student with empty score list
//   - void addScore(T student, int score): append score; throw
//     IllegalArgumentException if score not in 0-100
//   - double getAverage(T student): average of their scores;
//     throw IllegalStateException if no scores
//   - T getTopStudent(): student with highest average
//     (assume at least one enrolled student with scores)
//
// In main():
//   - Enroll 3 students, add varied scores
//   - Print each student's average
//   - Print the top student

